===Etymology===
From {{inh|ja|ojp|-|sort=はま}}, from {{inh|ja|jpx-pro|*pama}}. First attested in the ''{{w|Kojiki}}'' of 712 {{CE}}.<ref>{{R:Nihon Kokugo Daijiten 2|浜}}</ref>

In reference to palm trees being at a beach and other phonetic and semantic similarities, compare:
* {{cog|ine-pro|*pleh₂-|t=flat, broad, plain}}, whence:
** {{cog|la|plaga|t=area}}
*** {{cog|oc|plaja|t=beach}}
* {{cog|tai-pro|*haːtᴰ|t=beach; sand bar}}, whence:
** {{cog|th|หาด|tr=hàat|t=beach; sand bar}}
* {{cog|ine-pro|*pl̥h₂meh₂|t=palm of the hand|pos=also derived from {{cog|ine-pro|*pleh₂-|t=flat, broad, plain}}}}, whence:
** {{cog|itc-pro|*pəlmā}}
*** {{cog|la|palma|t=a palm tree}}
**** {{cog|en|palm|t=a palm tree}}

The beach senses seem more likely, but even so if comparing and deriving any from non-Japonic languages, the semantic and phonetic sound changes are yet to be explained, so possibly just coincidental.

